), and adding in its place, a semicolon, to read as follows: ยง682.402 Death, disability, closed school, false certification, and bankruptcy payments. (a) General. (1) Rules governing the payment of claims based on filing for relief in bankruptcy, and discharge of loans due to death, total and permanent disability, attendance at a school that closes, and false certification by a school of a borrower's eligibility for a loan, are set forth in this section. (2) If a PLUS loan was obtained by two parents as co-makers, or a Consolidation loan was obtained by a married couple, and only one of the borrowers dies, becomes totally and permanently disabled, has collection of his or her loan obligation stayed by a bankruptcy filing, or has that obligation discharged in bankruptcy, the other borrower remains obligated to repay the loan.
